h3. h3. Description (by Eric): 

In Space Settings > Permission > Edit Permission on an individual user (a new test user that you created or invite in Site Admin settings or any existing user) and remove permission to add or delete a comment in Comment forum and save. 

Go to any given page and create a comment as admin. Then log out and log in as the user with permission modified, observe that they still have permission to add new comment or delete their comment and other people comment. 
h3. h3. Investigation note (by Cherie):

This is a backend issue.

After logged in as the permission modified user. Frontend calls the following query to get operations permissions. Based on the response, frontend decides whether to show add comment input box or not. In this example, when comment and attachments create permission has been disabled, there should be no `{"operation":"create","targetType":"comment","__typename":"OperationCheckResult"},{"operation":"create","targetType":"attachment","__typename":"OperationCheckResult"}` in the response. However, the backend still returns these two permissions. 

 

POST API: /wiki/rest/graph?q=spaceInfo

